11/01/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Visiting Danish Defence Minister Gitte Lillelund Bech voiced support on Monday (January 10th) for Serbia's EU bid and praised Belgrade's contribution to regional stability.
Bech and Serbian counterpart Dragan Sutanovac discussed co-operation between their ministries, assessing it as very good.
They attended a ceremony for the signing of a bilateral military agreement that envisions more than 30 joint activities this year.
Sutanovac said Denmark is interested in co-operation regarding the military base in Bujanovac that is to become a regional centre for peacekeeping operations.
(Tanjug, RTS, Beta - 10/01/11)
